records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, credit for 0 days, Huber privileges for AODA treatment and child care. IMPOSED and STAYED. 
The Court placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years.  
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
-No violations of State or Federal law that rise to the level of probable cause
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-Mental health assessment and any recommended treatment to include any counseling, therapy and taking any prescribed medications
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification course
-Successfully complete a parenting course
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be paid by 7/24/17; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay related surcharge by 7/24/17; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
The Court makes the defendant eligible for expunction.
Sentence to commence FORTHWITH.

Defendant Andrea L Luedke in court with attorney Anne A. Devitt.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for Nick Cerwin for the State of Wisconsin.   Court orders stayed warrant lifted. Defendant  advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.   Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised she is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms; also defendant is advised she is unable to vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.
